\mathcal H
C< \mathcal H
x_0\in\mathcal H\setminus C
\eta:=d(x_0, C)=\displaystyle\inf_{c\in C}\left\lVert x_0- c\right\rVert
\hat c\in C
\eta=\left\lVert x_0- \hat c\right\rVert
\mathcal H
\hat c
C
\mathcal{H}=\ell^2
x_i\in\ell^2
C = \{x_i|i\in\mathbb{N}\}
x_i(n) = \begin{cases} 1+\frac{1}{n+1} & n=i \\ 0 & n\neq i\end{cases}.
0\in\mathcal{H}\backslash C
\inf_{c\in C}\|0-c\| = \inf_{i\in\mathbb{N}}\|x_i\| = \inf_{i\in\mathbb{N}} \left(1+\frac{1}{i+1}\right)=1.
